CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 17, 1959, pg. 27 reads: "Fight for Ball - Players from Schenley and Peabody fight for possession of a rebound in Section 1 action on the former's court. Peabody won a close one, 67-66, to tie Fifth Avenue for first place.  Schenley's Elmer Holiday poured in 31 points in lost cause, while John Wideman with 21, and Max Holm with 20, led Peabody scorers. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Schenley and Peabody basketball players, including Elmer Holiday, John Wideman, and Max Holm, playing on gymnasium court with referee
